==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: al-
<hw>al-</hw>. <pos>prefix.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd> <ety>[AS.
<ets>eal</ets>.]</ety> <def>All; wholly; completely; <as>as,
<ex>al</ex>mighty, <ex>al</ex>most</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <ety>[L.
<ets>ad</ets>.]</ety> <def>To; at; on; -- in OF. shortened to
<xex>a-</xex>. See <er>ad-</er>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The Arabic
definite article answering to the English <it>the</it>; <as>as,
<ex>Al</ex>koran, <it>the</it> Koran or <it>the</it> Book;
<ex>al</ex>chemy, <it>the</it> chemistry.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

